<header class="container">
  <hgroup>
    <h1>Peegee</h1>
    <p>Secure Password Generator</p>
  </hgroup>
</header>

<main class="container">
  <section>
    <article>
      <header>
        <h2>Use as MCP Server</h2>
      </header>
      <p>Peegee works as an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server. You can use it from VSCode, Claude Code, and more.</p>

      <details>
        <summary><strong>VSCode Setup</strong></summary>
        <p>Add this to your config file (.vscode/mcp.json):</p>
        <pre><code>{
  "servers": {
    "Peegee": {
      "type": "sse",
      "url": "<%= request.base_url %>/mcp/sse"
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary><strong>Claude Code Setup</strong></summary>
        <ol>
          <li>Run this command in your console:</li>
          <li><code>claude mcp add --transport sse peegee <%= request.base_url %>/mcp/sse</code></li>
          <li>If Claude Code is running, restart it</li>
        </ol>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary><strong>Available Tools</strong></summary>
        <ul>
          <li><code>peegee_generate_standard_password</code> - Generate standard password</li>
          <li><code>peegee_generate_japanese_secret_question_password</code> - Generate password for Japanese secret questions</li>
          <li><code>peegee_generate_kuroneko_password</code> - Generate password for Kuroneko Members</li>
          <li><code>peegee_generate_nenkin_password</code> - Generate password for Nenkin Net</li>
          <li><code>peegee_generate_sbisec_password</code> - Generate password for SBI Securities</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </article>
  </section>

